			<div class="content" id="post-content-4804956">
									

<p>Just an idea I thought of one day while asking myself a question: How would the Foundation react if there was a way to escape the Earth and the myriad of anomalies it holds? This is the result.<br />
Wow this evolved into something completely different. Okay then. Changed into a story of the Foundation majorly screwing up by underestimating an anomaly, which promptly played them like a fiddle and breached containment.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Show&nbsp;Edit&nbsp;revision&nbsp;log&nbsp;+</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Close&nbsp;-</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>EDIT: Chose a path. Updated Accordingly. Thanks Quadraginta for the advice!<br />
EDIT II: Redid my idea a bit in response to crit. Thanks Nagiros for the advice!<br />
EDIT III: Adding in what is contained within my third response from Nagiros due to positive feedback via PM (they currently have IRL commitments, and thus can't continue the crit).<br />
EDIT IV: Received a green light from Quadraginta (woohoo!), editing my concept accordingly. Thanks again for the crit!</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>Seeking Greenlights:</strong> Yes</p>
<p><strong>Page Type:</strong> SCP Article</p>
<p><strong>Genre:</strong> Sorrowful, Dramatic, and Emotional (with undertones of Mystery)</p>
<p><strong>Page Layout:</strong> Standard format (with ACS), followed by an updated file</p>
<p><strong>Elevator Pitch:</strong> A blissful, temperate beach full of beautiful flora (no fauna) and a calming aura. Better yet, there's a gateway to a pocket dimension with more paradisal biomes within, and the entry's free! Sounds great, right? But what if it was all a lie?</p>
<p>Enter <em>Floreo situ-vasta</em>, the verdant overgrowth. A parasitic species of anomalous plant, loaded with extremely potent hallucinogens capable of producing powerful hallucinations. The beach is simply a hallucination caused by secreted hallucinogens in gaseous form.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p><strong>Central Narrative:</strong> The portal is opened through a large burst of thaumic energy (not confirmed, but the Foundation suspects an untrained yet powerful reality bender accidentally opened this), which draws the attention of the Foundation.</p>
<p>Foundation agents find the beach (in actuality a nest, but by the time the nest is in sight the agents are already under the hallucinogen's influence) and see what is described above. The portal itself doesn't lead to a pocket dimension, rather, a small planet (or moon) that got infested by these parasites. Due to the hallucinogens however, the Foundation agents recognise it as a pocket dimension.</p>
<p>The Foundation builds a Site around the beach to contain it, and mostly forget about it (an easily containable, low-risk anomaly). However, the Site soon succumbs to the plants (a splinter nest), and the plants' plan (part of a large hive mind, the largest section on the other side of the portal) begins.</p>
<p>Using hallucinations, it convinces the members of the Site that the world is in danger via a hallucinated email from the 05s to two high-ranking members of the Site (both of the Ethics Committee), and that evacuation plans should begin immediately.</p>
<p>Stuff happens (see my response to Quadraginta's second crit below), and everyone becomes infested by the plants, which begin spreading uncontrolled across the country. Eventually, the Foundation investigates the Site which is no longer responding, and find a massive plant hive spreading across the continent. The document ends with the Foundation researching ways to destroy the plant hive without killing everyone infested by it (might be a weak ending, needs crit).</p>
<p><strong>Hook/Attention Grabber:</strong> While somewhat similar to <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-778">SCP-778</a>, this Paradise is in fact being freely offered and can be seen. I believe it is different enough from that SCP that it can be considered a completely seperate idea.</p>
<p><strong>Additional Notes:</strong> See my responses for more detail.</p>
<p>Thanks for reading!</p>
</div>
