<p>Honestly, I'm pretty down for this idea, but you're gonna actually have to choose one of your three potential paths.</p>
<p>I'll briefly touch on all three.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+Yeet</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-Yeet</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>1.) This one intrigues me the most. It's a thing that is good, wholly good and purely beneficial. The catch? There's only so much room and if enough people find out and want in, people are likely gonna have to try to fight their way in, or try to force their way in somehow, staining and tainting this paradise with human greed. It's not even a Series 1 style compulsion effect, it's just people being people and being selfish because people want good things.</p>
<p>2.) This one kinda bores me. Very tropey, 'yeah, good stuff, we promise!' with an evil villain mustache twirl. It could work wonderfully with good execution, but eh.</p>
<p>3.) The third one is just a different version of 2. A tropey, 'yeah, good stuff, we promise, it's just that it's good for us and not you, never said it was good for you!' This can also work with good execution, but the simple existence of a paradise that humans greedily flock towards interests me most.</p>
<p>But that's just me.</p>
<p>I recommend reaching out to some reviewers on <a href="/butterfly-squad-roster">the butterfly squad</a> for some more insight.</p>
<p>I hope I helped and I bid you a lovely day, partner.</p>
<p>👍</p>
