<p>Summoned by PM.</p>
<p>I'm not sure I'm really tracking with the ethical dilemma you're presenting here. It's a paradisal pocket dimension with limited space, and that presents a problem to the Foundation why? Ideal tourist locations and life-saving medical care already exist in the real world and there isn't a mass panic over their artificial scarcity, mostly because access to those resources are controlled — the same thing the Foundation would do. I'm just not seeing why this circumstance is particularly challenging to the Foundation when their modus operandi is hiding supernatural objects, which are sometimes beneficial, to prevent mass panic.</p>
<p>Additionally you've got a couple elements here that seem&#8230; out of place. I'm not sure what the character of the guardian brings to this story, nor what information they could relay that isn't apparent. Likewise with the initial fake iteration, when there doesn't seem to be any interesting information presented.</p>
<p>Lastly regarding the discovery — generally you should try to shy away from anomalies being found in the tall grass, as it were, unless there's some deeper story reason why the Foundation specifically came across this.</p>

