<p>The introduction of imminent conflict is definitely an improvement since it forces the Foundation to act in uncharacteristic ways and draws readers in the see the conclusion. My main question now becomes how you're going to execute this new vision: the Foundation grappling with this limited space problem but not immediately investing on the face of it, given how&#8230; &quot;constructed&quot; the whole thing feels.</p>
<p>Are you going to focus on the lore of garden, or look at a couple characters with different takes on the situation, or drop into the story in a manner akin to <a href="/scp-4646">SCP-4646</a>?</p>
<p>If you want my take, I suggest you set up a fleshed-out protagonist and antagonist to argue over the space problem, weaving that into a more general exploration of Paradise's lore, and then end with a type of subversion or reveal.</p>

