			<div class="content" id="post-content-4822211">
									

<p>So I had an idea if I'm going to make this a part of the Competitive Eschatology. I've also decided to focus on a couple of protagonists here (through transcripts and emails, as both of them are high-ranking members of the ethics committee).</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Open&nbsp;Protagonists</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Close&nbsp;Protagonsists</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>Both protagonists are close friends, but here is where their opinions split. This will act as the turning point that fractures their relationship.</p>
<p>Protagonist 1 - For evacuating people into Paradise<br />
Has lost many people to the calamity that is Competitive Eschatology, including close friends and family members. Wants to see a bright future where no one has to suffer any more, and sees Paradise as a way to embody that future for everyone. Argues that Paradise seems completely harmless and is in fact beneficial for us. Ends up going into Paradise after a last, emotional goodbye to their friend.</p>
<p>Protagonist 2 - Against evacuating people into Paradise<br />
Has also lost people to Competitive Eschatology, including family and close friends. Wants to stop the suffering all over the world, but doesn't want to use anomalies out of distrust. Argues that 'Paradise' is incredibly suspicious in how it seems to be constructed for our desires. Ends up seeing their friend off into Paradise, but not entering it themselves.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Open&nbsp;Big&nbsp;Reveal</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Close&nbsp;Big&nbsp;Reveal</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>Big argument between everyone (Ethics Committee [the protagonists], 05 Council, etc.) on whether the use of this is ethically acceptable. Eventually, increasing pressure makes the Foundation use Paradise to evacuate a whole bunch of civilians (Veil be damned) and some scientists and members of the Foundation. Once the last person comes through (one of the protagonists), all of the wildlife goes quiet, the weather stops and becomes neutral rather than perfect, and the protagonist in Paradise walks on while the protagonist seeing their friend off realises something bad is happening and tries to leap into Paradise to save their friend. They don't make it in time.</p>
<p>An omnipresent voice speaks out, saying 'thank you for the sacrifices', and shuts the gate, before all hell breaks loose on the beach (the animals change, the fungi and plants begin spreading, the weather changes). The protagonist outside Paradise has most of their dominant arm cut off, and is left on the beach.</p>
<p>The beach changes into a hostile landscape inhabited by dangerous flora and fauna that quickly begin spreading, converting all the land they spread across into more of what is at the beach (foggy and misty, cold, numerous symbols everywhere on the plants, animals, and land).</p>
<p>While the protagonist is dying on the beach watching everything around them turn horrible, another entity appears on the beach. They have a brief conversation where the entity introduces itself as a primordial nature spirit attracted by the happenings on Earth as a means to gain power through sacrifices. The protagonist is understandably extremely angry, but the entity says that they won't be angry for much longer and walks off. Here, the protagonist dies.</p>
<p>There is then an updated version of the document that reflects the recent changes that occurred, along with updates on what is going on.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>To sum up the big reveal, the entity used the Paradise gateway as a means to get a bunch of sacrifices to increase its power (and harvest more sacrifices). It wants to spread itself as far as possible, and once it gets the sacrifices it uses them to change the beach into basically a spreading land virus that converts the land it touches into more of the spirit's domain to get even more sacrifices through victims.</p>
<p>Dunno if it's cliche or not, but I thought it fit the theme of Competitive Eschatology (specifically 'awakening'). Hope this is satisfactory!</p>

							</div>

								
