<p>Thanks for the recrit!</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Here&nbsp;are&nbsp;some&nbsp;responses&nbsp;in&nbsp;return!</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Wooooooooosh</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<blockquote>
<p>In other words, what aspect of this concept do you want to focus on?</p>
</blockquote>
<p>If I had to choose, the first part (the panic at the Site) would be my choice of focus. I feel the sense of mystery would be useful to keep readers driven to read and find out the solution. Driving force = mystery, panic, and ethical arguments between P1 &amp; P2.</p>
<p>And as another possible answer to your initial question (lessening of emotional impact), how about this, which happens as P1 is being rescued:<br />
- MTF is sent to rescue P1, and, as per <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">her</span> <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">their</span><sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-848870-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-848870-1')">1</a></sup> her instructions, the MTF members are equipped with gas masks<br />
- The MTF walk into the town, which is covered with plants (which slowly try to wrap around their legs)<br />
- After 15-20 mins they find her in a house (following her shouts and gunfire) strung up by large amounts of vines and plants, being dragged out of the window<br />
- P1 is freed by the MTF members, who all begin to walk out of the town<br />
- However, the gas masks, which seem effective at first, begin to fail as the thaumically charged gas begins working its way through the filters<br />
- When they are five minutes from making it out of the town the masks lose most of their effectiveness, and the MTF members begin hallucinating various things (fears, the town free of plants, their members dead, etc.)<br />
- They have to stop and get P1 to direct them verbally via radio<br />
- This initial explanation is interrupted by a large burst of light, followed by a strong gale coming from the gateway (this is the hive mind consuming the people’s thoughts, which creates a huge amount of thaumic energy that subsequently charges the plants covering the town)<br />
- As the MTF and P1 puzzle over this, the plants around them begin rapidly growing and blooming<br />
- P1 panics and tells the MTF members to run, hand in hand to not lose any members, while a member contacts the waiting team and asks for an immediate evacuation, which will arrive in 5 minutes<br />
- The MTF team tells her that she has to direct them out, as they can’t trust their vision, and P1 shakily agrees<br />
- Basicalky, the log follows P1 as she desperately tries to direct the MTF members and prevent their deaths<br />
- Inevitably, she isn’t able to save a couple of them<br />
- In the end, they are airlifted away as they watch the plants bloom and spread in a beautiful and horrifying display<br />
<span style="text-decoration: line-through;">-</span><br />
I’m really unsure about this one, but may serve as an emotional continuation to the Site (massive pressure placed upon P1 to save her saviours, and she is unable to fully do so). This may suffer from the same problem as my last suggestion, so please tell me if it does.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<br />
Anyway, thanks for reading, and hopefully this is suitable!
