			<div class="content" id="post-content-4843208">
									

<p><em>Returned for a third time. PM request.</em></p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<blockquote>
<p>It starts off with the spirit (I know you're unimpressed by the spirit, but I haven't thought of a replacement yet) creating a couple of large, strong animals capable of breaching containment (as a placeholder, think something like a rhino) that are still quite docile. The Foundation finds these, almost has a containment breach or two, logs them, and is now wary. But then no more appear, and the Foundation relaxes.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Mmmm considering the power of the plant's hallucinogenic properties, I don't see why it still needs to be a spirit and not just another hallucination from the plants. I get you wanted to have it use people as a form of</p>
<p>Anywho, this concept has shifted to something significantly more ambitious and with a <em>lot</em> of moving parts.</p>
<p>However, I can see that you're determined and I do feel a lot of love and care being put into this concept.</p>
<p>I feel as though this would be better suited as a Tale, but to be honest, I'm rather eager to see how you could pull this off as an article.</p>
<p>As a finicky, nitpicky individual, I'm always hesitant to give greenlights, but that's just me. There are several elements here that I wanted to argue against, before I remembered that other SCP articles did similar things and got away with it due to excellent execution.</p>
<p>Things to be wary of:</p>
<ul>
<li>writing in the hallucination aspect in a convincing manner that doesn't feel forced.</li>
<li>Writing an updated article after the main one.</li>
</ul>
<p>That said, I will give you this tentative <strong><span style="color: green">GREENLIGHT</span></strong>.</p>
<p>My intuition tells me you have a good handle on what kind of story you want to tell. I'm going to trust that intuition and see where it leads you.</p>
<p>Be sure to check out this page: <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-style-resource#toc3">http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-style-resource#toc3</a><br />
It gives you templates for the styles you wanted to use for this SCP, including emails and such.</p>
<p>Anywho, I bid you good luck with the rest of this piece as well as good luck with obtaining a second greenlight. Feel free to PM me if you need a draft crit later down the road.</p>
<p>Have a good day, mate!</p>
</div>
